{
  "texts": [
    "The CNN initiates by taking an input image and subjecting it to a series of convolutions and subsampling operations.",
    "Each convolution layer comprises a collection of filter matrices, which are multiplied with the preceding image matrix to extract significant features referred to as output channel maps.",
    "Subsequently, pooling layers are employed to decrease the dimensions of the input map while preserving crucial information.",
    "Max pooling, a subsampling Fig. 7 GAN architecture technique, selects the maximum value within each block.",
    "Nonlinearity is introduced into the network through activation functions like the rectified linear unit (ReLU), which sets negative values to zero."
  ]
}